dcterms:description: The Unified Medical Language System (UMLS) is a set of files and software that brings together many health and biomedical vocabularies and standards to enable interoperability between computer systems.
dcterms:title: Unified Medical Language System (UMLS)

dcterms:description: BioMed Central’s corpus provides access to a collection of full-text articles for text mining research, allowing researchers to analyze and extract information from biomedical literature.
dcterms:title: BioMed Central’s corpus

dcterms:description: A sample document related to the genetic overlap of three mental disorders, used as an example in the paper to illustrate the summarization method.
dcterms:title: Sample document related to genetic overlap of three mental disorders
